text: Kearney is a city in Nebraska, United States. It is in the south-central part of Nebraska. The city began in the late 19th century. The previous name of the city was Dobytown, but the area was later renamed Kearney. The 2020 Census recorded the population of Kearney at 33,790. The city has grown in recent years. ==References== Category:Cities in Nebraska Category:County seats in Nebraska Category:19th-century establishments in Nebraska
